cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for lossless data compression using recurrent neural networks. This involves learning models for sequential data and performing prediction-based compression. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the use of arithmetic coding, which falls under the sub-category cs.DC (Data Compression). Finally, since the paper uses neural networks as the main tool, it is also likely to fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
